<br>
If it's in a dungeon, melees rule. <br>
If it's in an outdoor zone, casters got better chances.<br>
<br>
I play a 60 nec on VZ and trust me, there is no such thing as a given win against an equal lvl character..<br>
<br>
You have to take into account what the opponent got gearwize....and itemwize.<br>
Golemwands rule. Oldstyle pumice rule.<br>
If you go up against an opponent with these, you will find yourself buffless in 1 sec flat.<br>
<br>
Some of the statements here are pretty funny <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;I dont think any caster at 40+ can stand and take the blasts from a full bar of wizard mana no matter if they got 200MR 200FR and 200CR all at the same time.&quot;<br>
<br>
A cleric can out heal this.<br>
A necro can outdrain this.<br>
A good melee will interrupt this.<br>
A SK will HT and drain you to death before the mana is gone.<br>
etc..<br>
<br>
&quot;At 50+ a Paladin or SK with good resists (i.e. BD Bracers etc...) should be able to beat anyone. &quot;<br>
<br>
From a necs view:<br>
SKs are awsome with HT disc and drains. For these the spectre unfearable pet is nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Stick with deflux, and never go below 1k hp if possible..cause then youre dead. HP gear is nice..*grin*. SKs are hard opponents.<br>
<br>
Pallys got LoH and heals (stunns will be resisted 95% of the time). Often they try to root the pet, just dispel it..If they go after you, you can just deflux until dead while running close to pet so it stays in meleerange of the pally. <br>
<br>
Mages with fearless epic pets are nasty..<br>
<br>
Rogues are evil when they get close..<br>
<br>
A well played enchanters are awsome, against casters they really shine..<br>
<br>
Warriors..lots of hp, stunkick..<br>
<br>
Bards..Almost unkillable outdoors unless they screw up.<br>
Dam you! You petpoofers! Dam you! (Sidenote: Thanks verrant for this awsome feature)<br>
<br>
Rangers..bows, melee..icky<br>
<br>
Druids..DoTs, DDs, DS...bearpet!!?! (JK)<br>
Needs to be dispelled golemwand style!<br>
<br>
Shamans..debuffs need to be dispelled asap! Nasty with SoWboots and DoTs. And that puppy pet can stun you unless it's taken care of. <br>
<br>
Anyway. A necro is neat..but the way verrant buffed melees after kunark is just sad. Tanks hitting for 300+ with tantors tusk..Rangers with UBR bows and trueshot hitting you while running and out of spell range..Rogues BSing for 1k..etc..<br>
<br>
Now they even upgraded melees more with the last patch.<br>
From a PvP standpoint this is crazy. Almost every high lvl caster on PvP servers makes melee twinks, mainly rogues, rangers and SKs.<br>
<br>
Against a necro resists don't really matter. All spells used are unresistable. (Try using EB and CoC against anyone with full BD, waste of mana)<br>
<br>
Drains, Vexing, Pyro, Anul, Jboots, Instacast items, Potions, Harmshield and SS are your friends...use them wisely!<br>
<br>
The comments about that PvP skills are best tested in the arena are at least in my oppinion false, cause using hills, trees and terrain should be a part of the fight. Hills and trees are very useful! Thats like the warrior saying to a wizzard: stand still f00! I can't hit you with my UBRweapon_03 if you run around and use spells!<br>
<br>
&quot;At lvl 60 I would have to say SK, using HT disc.&quot;<br>
Good call Secks, pretty much summs it up. <br>
<br>
Mkay..think im a bit off subject..it's late..I'm tired..Hope you can make something outta this post <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Top 5 things you need to be a good PvPer is skills, skills, skills, gear, luck.<br>
Skills to get the hit/spell off. Gear and Luck to have it not miss/fizzle/be resisted.<br>
